==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English [[nute]], from Old English [[hnutu]]. Cognate with Latin [[nux]], Dutch [[noot]], German [[Nuss]], Icelandic [[hnut]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|nŭt}}
*{{IPA|/nʌt/}}
*{{SAMPA|/nVt/}}

===Noun===
'''nut''' (''plural:'' '''[[nuts]]''')

#A hard-shelled seed.
#A piece of metal, often [[hexagonal]], with a hole through it with internal threading intended to fit on to a bolt.
#(''informal'') An insane person.
#(''slang'') The head.
#(''slang; rarely used in the singular'') A testicle.

====Synonyms====
*(''insane person''): [[loony]], [[nutcase]], [[nutter]]
*(''the head''): [[bonce]], [[noodle]] (See further synonyms under [[head]])
*(''a testicle''): [[ball]], [[bollock]] (''taboo slang''), [[nads]]

